    <weatherForecast/>
    <avalancheActivity>
      <highlights>The danger of moist and wet avalanches will increase quickly during the day.</highlights>
      <comment>Early morning: The surface of the snowpack will only just freeze. Where cloud cover will be heaviest during the night. &lt;br/> From late morning the natural activity of avalanches will increase. &lt;br/> In particular in starting zones where no previous releases have taken place and on very steep slopes more medium-sized and, in isolated cases, large natural wet avalanches are possible. &lt;br/> The conditions are generally favourable for ski touring. Backcountry tours and ascents to alpine cabins should be concluded timely. &lt;br/> &lt;br/> In the course of the day mostly small wind slabs will form especially above approximately 3000 m.</comment>
    </avalancheActivity>
    <snowpackStructure>
      <comment>The wind will be moderate in some localities. &lt;br/> The weather conditions gave rise to rapid settling of the snowpack. &lt;br/> At higher altitudes, snow cover becomes thinner and patchy; it is better at mid-altitudes, which are less exposed to the wind. Below approximately 2000 m hardly any snow is lying. &lt;br/> The weather conditions gave rise to moistening of the snowpack below approximately 2500 m. &lt;br/> Weak layers exist in the snowpack in particular on steep shady slopes.</comment>
    </snowpackStructure>
    <travelAdvisory/>
    <tendency>
      <highlights>More moist and wet avalanches are possible. &lt;br/> As a consequence of the moderate northwesterly wind, fresh snow drift accumulations will form.</highlights>
      <tendencyType>steady</tendencyType>
